{
  "stem": "13382.3",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, but I think before I go to that one, which is part of my life as well, my eldest brother Alex-- he reached the stage-- he reached the age when he has to call up to the army.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And because he was Jewish-- at that time, they never-- they didn't take any more Jews into the army-- but the army formed a sort of a working section, which the Jews who were called to the army, they were-- instead of getting into-- getting into the real army, they put them into this working section.",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so in 1942, he was called in and he left home.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was stationed in-- in Hungary for a while.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I mean, I think he was in Miskolc, which is a rather large city northwest from Budapest.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I went a couple of time to visit him.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And soon after, they were taken out of the country.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I think they were taken either to Poland or to Romania, you know, when--",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, they didn't wear uniform.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They just wear some sort of a-- some of them wear some army hat.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they had an armband, a yellow armband, which was representing that they are Jews.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But some had white armband, which represented that they are converted, Jews converted to Christianity.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah-- no, just an armband.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Just a color.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And so we had to start to organize our life.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The life became-- in a way it was good, because Budapest was a nice city, and we really enjoyed it.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "To make some sort of a living, money-- money was always sort of quite an important part of life, and especially in Budapest was more difficult, more expensive than.",
      "word_count": 29
    }
  ],
